# Vendor Submodules Overview

This directory contains external projects included as Git submodules. These are third-party libraries and tools that the `solfunmeme-dioxus` project depends on.

## Submodules:

*   **`vendor/AEADs`**: Authenticated Encryption with Associated Data (AEAD) implementations.
*   **`vendor/BLAKE3`**: The BLAKE3 cryptographic hash function.
*   **`vendor/MACs`**: Message Authentication Code (MAC) implementations.
*   **`vendor/QR-Code-generator`**: A QR code generator library.
*   **`vendor/SOLFUNMEME`**: Likely a core component or dependency related to the Solfunmeme project itself.
*   **`vendor/SolanaWalletAdapter`**: Adapters for integrating with Solana wallets.
*   **`vendor/addr2line`**: A library for converting addresses to source code locations.
*   **`vendor/adler2`**: Adler-32 checksum algorithm implementation.
*   **`vendor/agave`**: A Solana-related project, possibly a client or utility library.
*   **`vendor/agave-solana-validator`**: A local Solana validator for development and testing.
*   **`vendor/ahash`**: A fast, non-cryptographic hash function.
*   **`vendor/aho-corasick`**: An efficient string searching algorithm.
*   **`vendor/ai-agent-terraform`**: Terraform configurations for AI agent infrastructure.
*   **`vendor/alga`**: A linear algebra library.
*   **`vendor/algebra`**: Another algebra-related library.
*   **`vendor/android-tzdata`**: Android timezone data.
*   **`vendor/android_system_properties`**: Android system properties access.
*   **`vendor/anyhow`**: A flexible error handling library.
*   **`vendor/approx`**: A library for approximate floating-point comparisons.
*   **`vendor/arrayref`**: Utilities for creating array references.
*   **`vendor/arrayvec`**: A vector with a fixed capacity on the stack.
*   **`vendor/async-channel`**: Asynchronous multi-producer, multi-consumer channel.
*   **`vendor/async-lock`**: Asynchronous locking primitives.
*   **`vendor/async-trait`**: Macro for defining async traits.
*   **`vendor/atomic-waker`**: An atomic waker for asynchronous programming.
*   **`vendor/atty`**: A library to check if a stream is a TTY.
*   **`vendor/autocfg`**: Autoconfiguration for Rust crates.
*   **`vendor/axum`**: A web application framework.
*   **`vendor/bincode`**: A compact encoder/decoder for Rust values.
*   **`vendor/bitflags`**: A macro to generate `bitflags!` types.
*   **`vendor/block-ciphers`**: Implementations of various block ciphers.
*   **`vendor/block-modes`**: Block cipher modes of operation.
*   **`vendor/bm25`**: An implementation of the BM25 ranking function.
*   **`vendor/borsh`**: Binary Object Representation Serializer for Hashing.
*   **`vendor/borsh-rs`**: Rust implementation of the Borsh serialization format.
*   **`vendor/bs58-rs`**: Base58 encoding/decoding.
*   **`vendor/bumpalo`**: A fast bump allocation arena.
*   **`vendor/bv-rs`**: A bit vector library.
*   **`vendor/bytemuck`**: Utilities for safely reinterpreting bytes.
*   **`vendor/byteorder`**: Byte order conversions.
*   **`vendor/bytes`**: Utilities for working with bytes.
*   **`vendor/calloop`**: A small event loop library.
*   **`vendor/calloop-wayland-source`**: Wayland event source for calloop.
*   **`vendor/candle`**: A machine learning framework.
*   **`vendor/cfg_aliases`**: Aliases for `#[cfg]` attributes.
*   **`vendor/cfg_eval.rs`**: Evaluation of `#[cfg]` expressions.
*   **`vendor/chrono`**: Date and time library.
*   **`vendor/ciborium`**: CBOR serialization/deserialization.
*   **`vendor/client-toolkit`**: A toolkit for Wayland clients.
*   **`vendor/clipboard-win`**: Clipboard access for Windows.
*   **`vendor/concurrent-queue`**: A concurrent queue.
*   **`vendor/console_error_panic_hook`**: Panic hook for console errors.
*   **`vendor/console_log`**: Logging to the console.
*   **`vendor/const_format_crates`**: Compile-time string formatting.
*   **`vendor/constant_time_eq`**: Constant-time equality checking.
*   **`vendor/convert-case`**: Case conversion utilities.
*   **`vendor/copypasta`**: Cross-platform clipboard access.
*   **`vendor/core-foundation-rs`**: Rust bindings for Core Foundation.
*   **`vendor/crossbeam`**: Concurrency primitives.
*   **`vendor/crunchy`**: Utilities for working with slices.
*   **`vendor/crypto-bigint`**: Cryptographic big integers.
*   **`vendor/cryptocorrosion`**: Cryptographic primitives.
*   **`vendor/cursor-icon`**: Cross-platform cursor icons.
*   **`vendor/curve25519-dalek`**: Ristretto and Curve25519 operations.
*   **`vendor/curves`**: Elliptic curve cryptography.
*   **`vendor/darling`**: A proc-macro helper for parsing attributes.
*   **`vendor/dashmap`**: A concurrent HashMap.
*   **`vendor/data-encoding`**: Various data encodings.
*   **`vendor/derivation-path`**: BIP32 derivation paths.
*   **`vendor/derive_more`**: Custom derive macros.
*   **`vendor/dioxus`**: A React-like GUI library for Rust.
*   **`vendor/dioxus-charts`**: Charting components for Dioxus.
*   **`vendor/dioxus-clipboard`**: Clipboard integration for Dioxus.
*   **`vendor/dioxus-motion`**: Animation and motion for Dioxus.
*   **`vendor/displaydoc`**: A derive macro for `Display` trait.
*   **`vendor/dlib`**: A C++ library for machine learning (likely bindings).
